Fix saving user context.

Previously it produced a file like this:

$ cat context.yml
!!python/object/new:sw_cli.context_factories.Context
dictitems:
  SWCLI_GLOBAL_SECRETS: /home/kubag/.sw_cli/global-secrets
  SWCLI_MODE: development

Not it produces a "normal" YAML:

$ cat context.yml
SWCLI_GLOBAL_SECRETS: /home/kubag/.sw_cli/global-secrets
SWCLI_MODE: development

Allow configuring logging level. Make INFO the default one.

The level can be configured by:
* running a command with "--verbose" flag, which sets the level to DEBUG
* setting "SWCLI_LOG_LEVEL" to any level in user context file, typically
  stored in ~/.sw-cli/context.yml which uses that level for all
  commands

Use rsync when uploading files to GCS.

If files don't change, it's better to use "rsync" than "cp".
Thanks to that, only changed files will be uploaded.
I chose to use option "-c" to compare files based on size and
checksums, instead of mtime, which work more reliably.
Docs: https://cloud.google.com/storage/docs/gsutil/commands/rsync

Remove bind mounting minikube directories.

Alternative fix is to add run the following command on host machine:

  echo "d /tmp 1777 root root 1s" | sudo tee /etc/tmpfiles.d/tmp.conf
  echo "x /tmp/hostpath-provisioner/*" | sudo tee -a /etc/tmpfiles.d/tmp.conf
  echo "x /tmp/hostpath_pv/*" | sudo tee -a /etc/tmpfiles.d/tmp.conf
